comments.body:
@mattleibow I think the expectation would be for the event to never fire in the infinite-loop scenario.

But your question makes me realize the idea can be improved, by splitting this into two events: `OnFinishedLoop` and `OnFinishedPlayback`.

`OnFinishedLoop` would fire on completion of each loop, and `OnFinishedPlayback` would fire on completion of the final loop (if any).
